text: my favorite dish during christmas is you
log a holdover from the days of french
colonialism
eulog is a french edition of bhushan
nuan first arrived in vietnam during the
late 19th century and known locally as
bangkok yanson the thick and spongy raw
cake grew into something of a luxury
item on christmas given the cost of
ingredients and not to mention the oven
required to make it it's really charming
and yummy so give it a try
ingredients you will need 4 eggs 50 gram
raisins
90 gram powder sugar 2 grams salt
a teaspoon vanilla extract
30 gram vegetable oil 50 ml of milk 50
gram all-purpose flour 20 gram
cornstarch 2 gram baking powder and 2
gram cream of tartar firstly preheat
your oven at 175 degrees celsius or 350
fahrenheit separate 4 eggs
[Music]
combine 50 gram all-purpose flour with
20 grams of cornstarch 2 gram baking
powder and 2 gram salt in a bowl next
beat up the egg yolks gradually add 25
gram of powdered sugar beat well until
the egg yolks get thicker and turn pale
[Music]
next combine 50 ml of milk with 30 ml of
vegetable oil gradually add the milk and
oil mixture into the egg yolk mixture
stir well to incorporate now sift in 50
grams of all-purpose flour in two
additions then mix well until combined
add 50 gram of raisins then add the
vanilla extract and mix well
add half a teaspoon of cream of tartar
beat up the egg whites until you see big
bubbles appear gradually adding 65 grams
of powdered sugar and beat over medium
speed until the sugar is completely
dissolved continue beating until it gets
thicker and when you lift up the bitter
a hard pick is formed now take 1 3 of
the egg white and mix with the egg yolk
mixture use folding method to make
gently until homogeneous then pour this
mixture to the remaining egg white in
the larger bowl and use a spatula to
fold in the mixture run the spatula
along the sides of the bowl and lift up
in the center fold gently until you see
no trails of egg white in the mixture
then pour the mixture into a sheet pan
light with parchment paper my pan is 38
by 26 cm that's 10 by 15 inches spread
the mixture to fill the cake pan and
flatten the surface tap the pan on the
counter a few times to release all the
big bubbles inside bake the cake at 135
degrees celsius or 350 fahrenheit for
about 20 minutes when it's cooked
through and nicely golden brown place
another sheet of parchment paper on top
place a baking cooling rack on top then
flip over to unmold gently peel off the
parchment paper at the bottom of the
cake roll it up when it's still warm
then set aside for about half an hour
until it's completely cooled down
my u-lock this year will come with a
special cream cheese fillings you will
need 200 grams of cream cheese 50 gram
of raisins which is optional 50 grams of
powdered sugar 200 ml of whipping cream
and 50 gram chocolate chips chill the
cream and the bowl in the freezer for
about 15 minutes before beating beat up
the whipping cream until soft big formed
then chill in the refrigerator next beat
up the cream cheese until fluffy add 50
gram of powdered sugar and continue
beating until incorporated combine the
whipping cream with the cream cheese in
four additions folding gently each time
until incorporated
next unroll the cake spread half of the
cream cheese mixture to fill the inside
of the cake sprinkle with raisins if
preferred roll up the cake again keeping
the seal side down chill the cake in the
refrigerator for about 30 minutes so the
cream will get firmer in a small bowl
combine 50 gram of chocolate chip with a
tablespoon of milk or whipping cream
then microwave for 30 seconds until
melted leave to cool and combine with
the rest of the cream cheese fillings
mix well until homogeneous
now remove the raw cake from the fridge
measure the cake stand cut the roll cake
into two pieces the larger piece should
fit your cake stand cut the smaller
piece in half on a bias place it to the
side of the cake like a branch of the
log then cover the cake with the
chocolate cream cheese use a fork to
create butter lines in the cake then
cover with powdered sugar which looks
like snow and you will have a little
sweet christmas for yourself i wish you
a merry and blessful christmas with your
beloved thank you for watching and i
will see you next time bye
[Music]
